title: Independent Ameer Farzand Khan wins PK-56 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Ameer Farzand Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa (KP) Assembly election from PK-56, Mardan-III by securing 33,430 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Awami National Party (ANP) candidate Abdul Aziz who bagged 16,823 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 40.37 percent.
